targets.target: get link_name, node, aggregate(values.input, 60, average),aggregate(values.output, 60, average) between (1570571291, 1570657691) by link_name from interface where (link_name like ".+")

panels.content:
# Table + Heat Maps for volume/rate

A table of data showing recent data flows between Swain Hall and DC-WAN, as well as heat maps for volume and rate that allow easier identification of patterns

# Heat Map perfSONAR loss data

A HeatMap of perfSONAR loss data to identify patterns of occurrence

targets.target: get source_description, destination_description, aggregate(values.loss, 3600, average) between ($START,$END) from ps_owamp where  ( source_description = "$source" and destination_description = "$destination" )

panels.content:
# Other Features

On the other hand, a campus CI engineer might want to know more about what labs are dominating the use of a given link. The Dashboard in this case might have a similar map (explained in Section 5.A), but would also contain information about the Top Talkers (explained in 5.E), and perhaps a Sankey graph of flow information

1. map
2. top Talkers
3. sankey graph of flow information
